FBIS3-28829 "dreas030__a94016" FBIS-EAS-94-030-A Document Type:Daily Report 14 February 1994 ANNEX Mongolia Social Democrats Urge National Leaders Resign OW0302162994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1351 GMT 3 Feb 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0302162994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 3 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The Mongolian Democratic Association which was the first to be set up in Mongolia has made public its intention to intensify its activities. Another opposition force the Social Democratic Party suggested leaders of the parliament N. Bagabandi and J. Gombojav and Prime Minister P. Jasray to resign. This step of the opposition forces was prompted by the accusations of top ranking dignitaries to have been involved in corruption and other sins. Having steadily been done by former chief of the counterintelligence Colonel L. Sanjaasuren. The leadership of the major opposition force being the National Democratic Party has gathered to hold a meeting during which it would obviously be worked out their party's position on this matter.
